/wiki/Karim_Betina: Karim Betina is a Paralympian athlete from Algeria competing mainly in category F32 shot put and club throw events.
/wiki/Athletics_at_the_2008_Summer_Paral: Athletics at the 2008 Summer Paralympics were held in Beijing National Stadium from September 8 to September 17. There were 160 gold medals in this sport.
The Men's Shot Put F32 had its Final held on September 8 at 17:05.
/wiki/Kamel_Kardjena: Kamel Kardjena (born May 26, 1981) is a Paralympic athlete from Algeria. He has cerebral palsy and competes in seated throwing events in the F33 classification.
/wiki/Athletics_at_the_2008_Summer_Paral: The Men's Shot Put F33-34/52 had its Final held on September 12 at 17:00.
/wiki/Mouloud_Noura: Mouloud Noura (born 30 December 1982) is an Algerian Paralympic judoka. He represented Algeria at the 2008 Summer Paralympics, at the 2012 Summer Paralympics and at the 2016 Summer Paralympics. He won two medals: the gold medal in the men's 60 kg event in 2008 and one of the bronze medals in the men's 60 kg event in 2012.
/wiki/Judo_at_the_2008_Summer_Paralympic: The Judo competition of the 2008 Summer Paralympics was held in Beijing Workers' Gymnasium from September 7 to September 9. There were 13 events, corresponding to seven weight classes for men and six for women. At the Paralympics, judo is contested by visually impaired athletes.

The men's 60 kg judo competition at the 2008 Summer Paralympics was held on September 7 at the Beijing Workers' Gymnasium. Preliminary rounds started at 12:00 pm CST. Repechage finals, semifinals, bouts for bronze medals, and the final were held at 5:00 pm CST.
The men's 66 kg judo competition at the 2008 Summer Paralympics was held on September 7 at the Beijing Workers' Gymnasium.
/wiki/Sofiane_Hamdi: Sofiane Hamdi (born 22 August 1989) is a Paralympic athlete from Algeria competing mainly in category T37 sprint events.
/wiki/Athletics_at_the_2008_Summer_Paral: The Men's 200m T37 had its First Round held on September 15 at 10:59 and the Final on September 16 at 17:17.
/wiki/Samir_Nouioua: Samir Nouioua (born 10 July 1985) is a Paralympian athlete from Algeria competing mainly in category T46 middle distance events.
/wiki/Athletics_at_the_2008_Summer_Paral: The Men's 800m T46 had its First Round held on September 14 at 20:27 and the Final on September 15 at 17:24.
/wiki/Louadjeda_Benoumessad: Louadjeda Benoumessad (born 1 January 1982) is a Paralympian athlete from Algeria competing mainly in category F34 javelin throw events.
/wiki/Athletics_at_the_2008_Summer_Paral: The 'Women's javelin throw F33–34/52–53 had its Final held on September 13 at 17:00.
/wiki/Mounir_Bakiri: Mounir Bakiri is a Paralympian athlete from Algeria competing mainly in category F32 shot putt events.
/wiki/Hocine_Gherzouli: Hocine Gherzouli, (Arabic:حسين غيرذل) is a Paralympian athlete from Algeria competing mainly in category F40 shot put events.
/wiki/Athletics_at_the_2008_Summer_Paral:
The men's shot put F40 event at the 2008 Summer Paralympics took place at the Beijing National Stadium at 09:50 on 15 September. There was a single round of competition; after the first three throws, only the top eight had 3 further throws.
The competition was won by Paschalis Stathelakos, representing  Greece.
The Men's 100m T37 had its competition held on September 12, with the first round at 9:25 and the Final at 17:45.
The Men's 1,500m T46 had its First Round held on September 9 at 9:55 and the Final on September 10 at 18:46.
/wiki/Zine_Eddine_Sekhri: Zine Eddine Sekhri is a Paralympian athlete from Algeria competing mainly in category T13 middle distance events.
/wiki/Athletics_at_the_2008_Summer_Paral: The Men's 800m T13 had its Final held on September 15 at 17:34.
/wiki/Nadia_Medjemedj: Nadia Medjmedj  (born 20 March 1974) is a Paralympian athlete from Algeria competing mainly in category F56 shot put and discus throw events.
/wiki/Athletics_at_the_2008_Summer_Paral:
The women's shot put F57/58 event at the 2008 Summer Paralympics took place at the Beijing National Stadium at 17:00 on 9 September.
There was a single round of competition; after the first three throws, only the top eight had 3 further throws.
The competition was won by Eucharia Njideka Iyiazi, representing  Nigeria.
/wiki/Zoubida_Bouazoug: Zoubida Bouazoug (born 25 January 1976) is an Algerian judoka who won bronze medals in the + 70 kg weight class at both the 2008 and 2012 Summer Paralympics.
/wiki/Judo_at_the_2008_Summer_Paralympic: The women's +70 kg judo competition at the 2008 Summer Paralympics was held on September 9 at the Beijing Workers' Gymnasium. Preliminary rounds started at 12:00 pm CST. Repechage finals, semifinals, bouts for bronze medals, and the final were held at 5:30 pm CST.
/wiki/Athletics_at_the_2008_Summer_Paral:
The women's discus F57/58 event at the 2008 Summer Paralympics took place at the Beijing National Stadium at 17:00 on 16 September.
There was a single round of competition; after the first three throws, only the top eight had 3 further throws.
The competition was won by Eucharia Njideka Iyiazi, representing  Nigeria.
/wiki/Algeria_at_the_2008_Summer_Paralym: Algeria sent a delegation to compete at the 2008 Summer Paralympics in Beijing, People's Republic of China.
